<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-09T17:04:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-09T17:04:00-05:00" n="575" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17384</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-09T15:00:00-07:04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1916, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Gutierrez has informed me of Columbus attack by Villa requesting
                            that I inform the Government of the United States that orders have been
                            given for capture of the banditti from Mexican side.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>